      <!-- Section 6: Role of Schema Markup -->
      <section id="schema-role" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>The Role of Schema Markup in Answer Box Strategy</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>Schema markup is not the primary mechanism for winning Google featured snippets — content structure is — but it plays a critical supporting role by expanding the surface area of extractable content and by significantly improving citation rates on AI platforms beyond Google.</strong>
          Understanding the distinction matters because it affects where you invest optimisation effort.
        </p>

        <p>
          For Google featured snippets, the content structure signals (query-mirroring headings, direct definition-style answers, semantic HTML) are primary. Schema markup does not override these. A page with excellent structure but no FAQPage schema can win a featured snippet; a page with perfect FAQPage schema but poor content structure will not. The schema contribution is indirect: it increases Google's confidence in the content's authority and accuracy, which may contribute at the margin for competitive queries.
        </p>

        <p>
          For Google AI Overviews, FAQPage schema becomes more directly influential. AI Overview systems use structured data to identify and extract Q&A content more efficiently than prose extraction alone. A page with FAQPage schema and well-structured answers is easier for the AI Overview system to process as a citation source, particularly for conversational and follow-up queries where the schema's question-answer structure maps directly to the conversational context.
        </p>

        <p>
          For non-Google AI platforms — Perplexity, ChatGPT Browse, Gemini — FAQPage schema combined with TechArticle or Article schema provides the clearest structured signal of page type, authority, and content format. These platforms do not have access to a featured snippet signal equivalent to Google's — schema markup is the closest substitute for that kind of structured content endorsement. Implementing both <a href="/schema-markup-ai/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">schema markup for AI</a> and content structure optimisation delivers returns across the full platform set.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 7: Optimisation Checklist -->
      <section id="implementation" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>Answer Box Optimisation Checklist</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>A systematic answer box optimisation programme works through a fixed sequence: identify target queries, audit existing coverage, apply structural changes, validate HTML, and monitor positions.</strong>
          The checklist below covers the full sequence for a content page targeting one or more featured snippet positions.
        </p>

        <div class="not-prose mt-6 space-y-4">

          <div class="card p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Query Research and Prioritisation</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-300">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Identify queries for which a featured snippet exists (use Semrush, Ahrefs, or manual Google search review)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Confirm the snippet format for each query (paragraph, list, or table)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Confirm your page ranks in the top 10 for each target query (prerequisite for eligibility)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Prioritise queries where a competitor currently holds the snippet (displacement opportunity) over queries with no snippet (creation required)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Content Structure</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-300">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Add or update an H2 or H3 subheading that closely mirrors the target query question</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Place the direct answer immediately under the subheading — no preamble</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> For paragraph snippets: write the answer in 45–55 words, beginning with "X is..." or "X refers to..."</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> For list snippets: use semantic <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;ol&gt;</code> or <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;ul&gt;</code> with 5–8 concise <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;li&gt;</code> items</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> For table snippets: use semantic <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;table&gt;</code> with <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;thead&gt;</code> and <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&lt;th scope="col"&gt;</code> — no merged cells</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Schema and AI Platform Readiness</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-300">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Add FAQPage schema with Q&A pairs matching the target queries (each answer self-contained, 2–4 sentences)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Add TechArticle or Article schema with <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">datePublished</code>, <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">dateModified</code>, author, and publisher referencing <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">&#123;"@id":"https://geooptimised.com/#organization"&#125;</code></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Add BreadcrumbList schema reflecting the page's topical hierarchy</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Validate all schema via Google Rich Results Test — zero errors</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ink-50 mb-3">Monitoring and Maintenance</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-300">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Track featured snippet positions weekly for all target queries</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Monitor for format changes on held snippets (Google may switch from paragraph to list — update content to match)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> Update <code class="text-xs bg-geo-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">dateModified</code> whenever content is revised — freshness is a tiebreaker on competitive snippets</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[var(--accent)] mt-0.5">&#9744;</span> When a snippet is lost: identify the page that displaced it, analyse its structural advantages, and revise accordingly</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>

        <p class="mt-8">
          For a full featured snippet audit — including competitive gap analysis and prioritised content recommendations — <a href="/contact/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">contact GEOoptimised</a>. Our programmes address both traditional featured snippet capture and the broader AI visibility picture across all major generative platforms.
        </p>
      </section>

